oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Performance - Tommy Emmanuel, C.G.P. - 2011-08-27
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance by and interview with guitarist Tommy Emmanuel from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on August 27, 2011. Companion to a Chet Atkins exhibit.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Tommy Emmanuel; John Knowles;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Concert performance and interview with guitarist Tommy Emmanuel. Interview conducted by Mick Buck. Includes questions from the audience. Performances include; To Be Or Not To Be; Unidentified medley of songs including Cannonball Rag; Windy And Warm; Nine Pound Hammer; Chaplin In New Shoes; excerpt of Lady Madonna; excerpt of Day Tripper; excerpt of A Taste Of Honey; excerpt of Blue Moon; Over The Rainbow; Struttin'; San Antonio Stroll (with John Knowles); Tennessee Waltz (with John Knowles);
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Atkins, Chet; Emmanuel, Tommy; Knowles, John; Country Music Hall of Fame & Museum (Nashville, Tenn.);
